### Media

Key Biscayne has its own local publications. *The Islander News*, a weekly community newspaper, served the area with an estimated circulation of 3,600 in 2020. Additionally, *Key Biscayne Magazine*, a lifestyle publication based in Miami, had a circulation of approximately 10,000 in 2020.

### Education

The [Miami-Dade County Public Schools](/Miami-Dade_County_Public_Schools) district oversees education for Key Biscayne residents. The Key Biscayne K–8 Center serves students from kindergarten through eighth grade. Middle school students also have the option of attending Ponce de Leon Middle School in [Coral Gables, Florida](/Coral_Gables,_Florida). High school students are zoned for [Coral Gables Senior High School](/Coral_Gables_Senior_High_School).

Since 2012, [MAST Academy](/MAST_Academy), a magnet school located on [Virginia Key](/Virginia_Key), has offered priority admission to eligible Key Biscayne residents for its Cambridge program, which has 1,100 seats.

The [Miami-Dade Public Library System](/Miami-Dade_Public_Library_System) operates the Key Biscayne Branch Library, a 6,000-square-foot (560 m²) facility that opened in January 1985. St. Agnes Academy, a Catholic private school affiliated with the [Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Miami](/Roman_Catholic_Archdiocese_of_Miami), serves students from pre-kindergarten to eighth grade at its 122 Harbor Drive location.

