### Hotels and condominiums controversy

The construction of numerous condominium complexes significantly contributed to the island's population growth. In 2007, residents approved a charter amendment requiring voter approval for future land use changes. However, in 2008, the village council proposed revising the charter, arguing that the referendum requirement infringed upon their responsibilities. Voters overwhelmingly rejected this proposal on November 4, 2008, by a margin of more than two-to-one.

### Other information

Key Biscayne is home to the [Tennis Center at Crandon Park](/Tennis_Center_at_Crandon_Park), which formerly hosted the [Miami Open](/Miami_Open_(tennis)) Tennis Tournament. The area also features a golf course and numerous facilities for water sports and fishing.

A 24/7 visitors center is available at the Village Hall, 88 West McIntyre Street #100, adjacent to the police station. Staff is available Monday through Friday, from 9 am to 5 pm.

